The paper deals with the problem of explaining the output of an anomaly detection system, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the proposed framework involves constructing anomaly detection benchmarks from real data sets, which suggests a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CR) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of several novel explanation approaches, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
